name: EB-004-Mercury
description:
Freddie Mercury (born Farrokh Bulsara; Stone Town, September 5, 1946—London, November 24, 1991) was a British singer, pianist and songwriter known for his work with the British rock band Queen, which he was part of from 1970 until the year of his death (1991). Freddie became known for his powerful tone of voice and his energetic performances that involved an interaction with the audience, having been regarded as one of the greatest artists of all time.
